trators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: Activists, British individuals, Females, Wizards            Glinda Crook              View source                         History                         Talk (1)                                   Glinda Crook   Biographical information  Nationality British[1]    Physical information  Species Human[1]   Gender Female[1]    Affiliation  Occupation Activist for the Campaign for Greater Freedom for Wizards[1]   Loyalty Campaign for Greater Freedom for Wizards[1]   [Source]    "Merlin's beard, surely we can celebrate one night of the year without worrying about the blessed Muggles." — Crook's opposition to Ministry Hallowe'en restrictions[src]  Glinda Crook was a witch who worked for the Campaign for Greater Freedom for Wizards. She spoke on behalf of the organisation in the Daily Prophet, stating its opposition to new Ministry of Magic regulations, which were intended to limit magical activity on Hallowe'en.[1]  Contents  1 Etymology 2 Behind the scenes 3 Appearances 4 Notes and references   Etymology Glinda means "pure; good" in Welsh. The last name Crook originates from the byname "Krókr" which means "crook; bend" in Old Norse. Behind the scenes The name Glinda might have been taken from the character Glinda the Good Witch in the Oz books first written by L. Frank Baum. Appearances Daily Prophet Newsletters (First mentioned) Notes and references   ↑ 1.0 1.1 1.2 1.3 1.4 1.5 Daily Prophet Newsletters, Issue 4              Categories         Categories:   Activists    British individuals    Females    Wizards           *Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links, meaning, at no additional cost to you, Fandom will earn a commission if you click through and make a purchase. Community content is available under CC-BY-SA unless otherwise noted.             Advertisement     Fan Feed        More Harry Potter Wiki     1 Sirius Black     2 Hufflepuff     3 Ravenclaw                       